Sentencas: Proton conducting BaCe0.9Y0.1O3-x (BCY10) thick films are deposited on cermet anodes made of nickel-yttrium doped barium cerate using electrophoretic deposition (EPD) technique.
Titulo: Electrophoretic deposition of dense BaCe0.9Y0.1O3-x electrolyte thick-films on Ni-based anodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: BCY10 powders are prepared by the citrate-nitrate auto-combustion method and the cermet anodes are prepared by the evaporation and decomposition solution and suspension method.
Titulo: Electrophoretic deposition of dense BaCe0.9Y0.1O3-x electrolyte thick-films on Ni-based anodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The EPD parameters are optimized and the deposition time is varied between I and 5 min to obtain films with different thicknesses.
Titulo: Electrophoretic deposition of dense BaCe0.9Y0.1O3-x electrolyte thick-films on Ni-based anodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The anode substrates and electrolyte films are co-sintered at 1550 degrees C for 2 h to obtain a dense electrolyte film keeping a suitable porosity in the anode, with a single heating treatment.
Titulo: Electrophoretic deposition of dense BaCe0.9Y0.1O3-x electrolyte thick-films on Ni-based anodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The samples are characterized by Held emission scanning electron microscopy (FE-SEM) and energy dispersion spectroscopy (EDS).
Titulo: Electrophoretic deposition of dense BaCe0.9Y0.1O3-x electrolyte thick-films on Ni-based anodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: A prototype fuel cell is prepared depositing a composite La0.8Sr0.2Co0.8
Titulo: Electrophoretic deposition of dense BaCe0.9Y0.1O3-x electrolyte thick-films on Ni-based anodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Fe0.2O3 (LSCF)-BaCe0.9Yb0.1O3-delta (10YbBC) cathode oil the co-sintered half cell.
Titulo: Electrophoretic deposition of dense BaCe0.9Y0.1O3-x electrolyte thick-films on Ni-based anodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Fuel cell tests that are performed at 650 C oil the prototype single cells show a maximum power density of 174 mW cm(-2).
Titulo: Electrophoretic deposition of dense BaCe0.9Y0.1O3-x electrolyte thick-films on Ni-based anodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells
